    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-26T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-26T08:00:00-05:00" n="555"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.5151/262: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-26T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 26, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 26—10:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. A recent Greek decree requires all foreigners established here to convert
                    into drachmas their entire earnings from business done or services rendered in
                    Greece. See the last paragraph of my despatch number 3042 of May 15.<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d555fn9">Not printed.</note> Although the Minister of Finance
                    promises benevolent enforcement he indicates that exceptional treatment will be
                    granted only upon individual application, the decision resting with the Greek
                    authorities as to who should be considered “established” and how badly he needs
                    his money at home. The British and French Legations have urgently requested
                    instructions from their respective Foreign Offices and in the event that
                    protests are made to the Greek Government the Department may wish to authorize
                    me to take parallel action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
